a_0.formal problem:
theorem
fixes N :: int
assumes h0 : "22^2 * 55^2 = 10^2 * N^2"
shows  "N = 121"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 What is the positive integer $N$ for which $$ 22^2 \times 55^2 = 10^2 \times N^2 \ ? $$ The final Answer is 121
 ### Proof
 \begin{align} 10^2\times N^2&=22^2\times55^2\\ &=\left(2^2\cdot11^2\right)\times\left(5^2\cdot11^2\right)\\ &=\left(2^2\cdot5^2\right)\times\left(11^2\cdot11^2\right)\\ &=10^2\times \left(11^2\right)^2\\
 &=10^2\times 121^2 \end{align} So $N=\boxed{121}$.
 *)

theorem
fixes N :: int
assumes h0 : "22^2 * 55^2 = 10^2 * N^2"
shows  "N = 121"
 proof-
